{"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift\/using-imported-c-functions-in-swift"},"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"patch":0,"minor":3},"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"anchor":"Overview","type":"heading","text":"Overview","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Swift imports any function declared in a C header as a Swift global function."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For example, consider the following C function declarations:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"occ","code":["int product(int multiplier, int multiplicand);","int quotient(int dividend, int divisor, int *remainder);","","struct Point2D createPoint2D(float x, float y);","float distance(struct Point2D from, struct Point2D to);"]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Here’s how Swift imports them:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["func product(_ multiplier: Int32, _ multiplicand: Int32) -> Int32","func quotient(_ dividend: Int32, _ divisor: Int32, _ remainder: UnsafeMutablePointer<Int32>) -> Int32","","func createPoint2D(_ x: Float, _ y: Float) -> Point2D","func distance(_ from: Point2D, _ to: Point2D) -> Float"]},{"anchor":"Use-a-CVaListPointer-to-Call-Variadic-Functions","type":"heading","text":"Use a CVaListPointer to Call Variadic Functions","level":3},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In Swift, you can call C variadic functions, such as "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"vasprintf(_:_:_:)"},{"type":"text","text":", using the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Swift "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Swift\/getVaList(_:)"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Swift\/withVaList(_:_:)"},{"type":"text","text":" functions. The "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"withVaList(_:_:)"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"function takes an array of "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Swift\/CVarArg"},{"type":"text","text":" values and provides a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Swift\/CVaListPointer"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"value within the body of a closure parameter, whereas the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"getVaList(_:)"},{"type":"text","text":" function"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"returns this value directly. With either function, you pass the resulting "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CVaListPointer"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"value as the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"va_list"},{"type":"text","text":" argument of the C variadic function."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For example, here’s how to call the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"vasprintf(_:_:_:)"},{"type":"text","text":" function in Swift:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["func swiftprintf(format: String, arguments: CVarArg...) -> String? {","    return withVaList(arguments) { va_list in","        var buffer: UnsafeMutablePointer<Int8>? = nil","        return format.withCString { cString in","            guard vasprintf(&buffer, cString, va_list) != 0 else {","                return nil","            }","","            return String(validatingUTF8: buffer!)","        }","    }","}","print(swiftprintf(format: \"√2 ≅ %g\", arguments: sqrt(2.0))!)","\/\/ Prints \"√2 ≅ 1.41421\""]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Swift only imports C variadic functions that use a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"va_list"},{"type":"text","text":" for their arguments."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"C functions that use the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"..."},{"type":"text","text":" syntax for variadic arguments are not imported, and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"therefore can’t be called using "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CVarArg"},{"type":"text","text":" arguments."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Call-Functions-with-Pointer-Parameters","type":"heading","text":"Call Functions with Pointer Parameters","level":3},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Whenever possible, Swift avoids giving you direct access to pointers. When importing"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"C function parameters, however, Swift maps pointer parameters to standard library"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"pointer types. The following tables use "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Type"},{"type":"text","text":" as a placeholder type name to indicate"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"syntax for the mappings."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For return types, variables, and arguments, the following mappings apply:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"rows":[[[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"C Syntax","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Swift Syntax","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"const Type *"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Swift\/UnsafePointer"},{"text":"<Type>","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Type *"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Swift\/UnsafeMutablePointer"},{"text":"<Type>","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]]],"header":"row","type":"table"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For class types, the following mappings apply:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"rows":[[[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"C Syntax","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Swift Syntax","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Type * const *"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Swift\/UnsafePointer"},{"text":"<","type":"text"},{"text":"Type>","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Type * __strong *"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Swift\/UnsafeMutablePointer"},{"text":"<","type":"text"},{"text":"Type>","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Type **"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Swift\/AutoreleasingUnsafeMutablePointer"},{"text":"<","type":"text"},{"text":"Type>","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]]],"header":"row","type":"table"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For pointers to untyped, raw memory, the following mappings apply:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"rows":[[[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"C Syntax","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Swift Syntax","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"const void *"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Swift\/UnsafeRawPointer"}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"void *"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Swift\/UnsafeMutableRawPointer"}],"type":"paragraph"}]]],"header":"row","type":"table"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"C function pointers are imported into Swift as closures with the C function pointer"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"calling convention, denoted by the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"@convention(c)"},{"type":"text","text":" attribute. For example, a function"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"pointer that has the type "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"int (*)(void)"},{"type":"text","text":" in C is imported into Swift as "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"@convention(c) () -> Int32"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If the type of the value pointed to by a C pointer cannot be represented by Swift,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"as is the case with an incomplete struct type, the pointer is imported as an "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OpaquePointer"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"content"}],"metadata":{"roleHeading":"Article","role":"article","modules":[{"name":"Swift"}],"title":"Using Imported C Functions in Swift"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Learn how to call imported functions that are declared in a C header."}],"seeAlsoSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift\/customizing-your-c-code-for-swift","doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift\/using-imported-c-structs-and-unions-in-swift","doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift\/using-imported-c-macros-in-swift"],"generated":true,"anchor":"Language-Interoperability-with-C-and-C++","title":"Language Interoperability with C and C++"}],"sections":[],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/swift\/using-imported-c-functions-in-swift"]}],"kind":"article","hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift"]]},"references":{"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift":{"role":"collection","url":"\/documentation\/swift","type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Build apps using a powerful open language."}],"title":"Swift","images":[{"identifier":"Swift-PageImage-card.png","type":"card"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift","kind":"symbol"},"Swift-PageImage-card.png":{"identifier":"Swift-PageImage-card.png","alt":"An orange Swift logo on a gradient background.","variants":[{"url":"\/images\/com.apple.Swift\/Swift-PageImage-card@2x.png","traits":["2x","light"]},{"url":"\/images\/com.apple.Swift\/Swift-PageImage-card~dark@2x.png","traits":["2x","dark"]}],"type":"image"},"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/using-imported-c-structs-and-unions-in-swift":{"kind":"article","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift\/using-imported-c-structs-and-unions-in-swift","abstract":[{"text":"Learn how Swift represents imported C structures and unions, including types with","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"bitfields and unnamed fields.","type":"text"}],"role":"article","title":"Using Imported C Structs and Unions in Swift","url":"\/documentation\/swift\/using-imported-c-structs-and-unions-in-swift"},"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/customizing-your-c-code-for-swift":{"title":"Customizing Your C Code for Swift","type":"topic","role":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift\/customizing-your-c-code-for-swift","kind":"article","abstract":[{"text":"Use the ","type":"text"},{"code":"CF_SWIFT_NAME","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" macro to group functions that have related behavior.","type":"text"}],"url":"\/documentation\/swift\/customizing-your-c-code-for-swift"},"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/using-imported-c-macros-in-swift":{"title":"Using Imported C Macros in Swift","type":"topic","role":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift\/using-imported-c-macros-in-swift","kind":"article","abstract":[{"text":"Use imported C-defined macros as constants.","type":"text"}],"url":"\/documentation\/swift\/using-imported-c-macros-in-swift"}}}